 were fitted to animals (bought something for money) for clearly stated/particular purposes, using (connected/related) factors and categories. 
 In the overall model, the specified covariates and 
 factors explain 77% of the difference/different version in price per 
 animal but in the purpose clearly stated/particular models, the explanatory power differs/changes from 68% for animals (bought something for money) for (formal, special events or series of actions) to 84% for animals (bought something for money) 
