 Except in the case of special celebration, the coefficient of live 
 weight is greater than that for age. For special celebration, age 
 is a more important (number or thing that changes) than weight (actually 
 the coefficient of weight is not (meaningful numbers)) because for the Muslim special celebration of Eid-el-Kabir, 
 animals below certain age are not good for murder. 
 The negative effect of age square, significant in 
 all cases except for rearing, trading and butchering, 
 point to/show that less higher cost is paid for older animals. 
